Olam Says CLSA Overstated Importance of Nigeria Incentives

-- B y   A n d r e w   H o b b s
-- 
2011-02-22T23:32:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/olam-says-clsa-overstated-importance-of-nigerian-incentives-on-earnings.html
  Olam International Ltd . said a CLSA
Asia Pacific Markets report overstated the importance of
Nigerian export incentives to its earnings. “The report
estimates that Nigerian incentives account for 30 percent to 40
percent of Olam’s profits,” Olam said today in a statement.
“This attribution is incorrect.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Hobbs at 
